WEBVTT

00:51.040 --> 00:52.000
Can I team up

00:54.080 --> 00:54.680
with you?

00:58.000 --> 00:58.760
Sure.

01:05.519 --> 01:07.880
Alright, everyone, put the plate you received

01:07.880 --> 01:10.039
into the box you were given.

01:11.280 --> 01:13.440
Pick up the hammer on your workbench.

01:13.960 --> 01:16.280
When I count down from three,

01:16.640 --> 01:18.520
break the plate.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.960
Three, two, one.

01:22.280 --> 01:22.840
Smash it!

01:25.640 --> 01:26.170
You do it.

01:26.280 --> 01:27.410
It's fine, you do it.

01:30.039 --> 01:32.000
Alright, you have 30 minutes

01:32.200 --> 01:35.039
to restore the porcelain plates you smashed.

01:35.800 --> 01:38.130
Use the tools provided on your workbench.

01:39.039 --> 01:39.600
Begin.

01:40.600 --> 01:42.660
Isn't it broken into too many pieces?

01:43.039 --> 01:45.039
Professor, but we don't know how to glue it.

01:45.039 --> 01:46.320
Use your talents.

01:46.560 --> 01:47.160
Hurry up.

01:48.560 --> 01:51.090
I... I think I smashed it into too many pieces.

01:51.759 --> 01:52.120
I'm fine.

01:52.120 --> 01:52.920
Hurry, hurry.

01:53.880 --> 01:54.560
Impossible.

01:54.560 --> 01:56.200
I shouldn't have hit it so hard.

01:56.200 --> 01:57.330
This is ridiculous.

02:31.200 --> 02:32.560
Do you need my help?

02:33.800 --> 02:34.400
No.

02:35.760 --> 02:36.620
I don't need it.

03:00.120 --> 03:01.720
Then help me throw it away.

03:08.560 --> 03:10.000
Time's up.

03:10.360 --> 03:12.320
Stop what you're doing.

03:12.560 --> 03:13.520
Let me take a look

03:13.520 --> 03:15.640
and check the fruits of your labor.

03:18.760 --> 03:20.040
This one fails.

03:20.600 --> 03:21.960
This fails.

03:23.280 --> 03:23.760
Fail.

03:24.600 --> 03:25.600
Is this okay, sir?

03:28.640 --> 03:29.760
This is acceptable, right?

03:29.760 --> 03:30.280
Thank you, sir.

03:30.280 --> 03:31.240
Did you try your best?

03:31.240 --> 03:31.840
I tried my best.

03:31.840 --> 03:32.900
I tried my best too.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.780
As long as you tried your best.

03:37.680 --> 03:39.400
Will this pass?

03:42.640 --> 03:44.770
I shouldn't have smashed it to pieces.

03:52.560 --> 03:53.200
It'll do.

03:54.840 --> 03:55.480
65 points.

03:57.120 --> 03:57.840
Only 65?

03:58.000 --> 03:58.360
What?

03:59.320 --> 04:00.850
Did you expect a full score?

04:01.080 --> 04:02.410
If you want a full score,

04:02.640 --> 04:04.720
you can take your diploma and graduate now.

04:04.720 --> 04:05.560
So fierce.

04:05.800 --> 04:07.130
Is it really necessary?

04:07.800 --> 04:09.080
Class, now

04:09.200 --> 04:11.880
pick up the hammers on your workbenches again.

04:12.080 --> 04:13.960
I will break your plates again.

04:14.440 --> 04:14.720
Here.

04:14.720 --> 04:15.400
Oh my God.

04:15.400 --> 04:16.640
We just fixed it.

04:17.320 --> 04:18.399
Okay, excuse me.

04:19.120 --> 04:20.450
Let me take some pieces.

04:20.880 --> 04:22.600
One piece, two pieces.

04:22.720 --> 04:23.560
Excuse me.

04:25.200 --> 04:27.040
I'll take one piece from each group.

04:27.040 --> 04:28.120
Starting now,

04:28.400 --> 04:30.330
you will take the remaining pieces

04:30.360 --> 04:31.690
and restore them again.

04:32.000 --> 04:32.480
No way.

04:32.560 --> 04:33.880
Sir, you took a piece away.

04:33.880 --> 04:34.760
It's incomplete.

04:34.760 --> 04:35.480
How are we supposed to fix it?

04:35.480 --> 04:35.810
Yeah.

04:35.840 --> 04:38.320
Are the porcelain pieces excavated from underground

04:38.320 --> 04:39.320
always complete?

04:39.880 --> 04:41.440
I will check it next class.

04:41.720 --> 04:42.600
Class dismissed. Goodbye.

04:42.600 --> 04:44.200
Goodbye, sir.

04:48.000 --> 04:48.520
Xu Xiao.

04:51.320 --> 04:53.360
Where are you going now?

04:53.600 --> 04:56.040
You don't need to worry about this assignment.

04:56.040 --> 04:57.440
I can finish it by myself.

04:58.280 --> 05:00.320
But we're in the same group.

05:02.280 --> 05:03.740
I'm used to working alone.

05:05.480 --> 05:06.210
Don't worry.

05:06.480 --> 05:07.740
Mr. Yue won't find out.

05:08.400 --> 05:09.400
I want to help too.

05:14.720 --> 05:16.380
I'm glad you teamed up with me.

05:17.800 --> 05:20.060
Otherwise, I would have been left alone.

05:21.720 --> 05:22.400
So,

05:23.440 --> 05:25.120
I want to do my best to help you.

05:32.120 --> 05:32.920
This is...

05:33.600 --> 05:35.320
This is the antique shop where I work.

05:35.320 --> 05:36.080
Work?

05:36.480 --> 05:39.280
Aren't you going to finish the assignment with me?

06:04.840 --> 06:05.960
Why do we

06:06.200 --> 06:08.360
have to come here to do the restoration?

06:08.360 --> 06:10.200
I have my own restoration tools here.

06:10.200 --> 06:11.720
They are more complete than the school's,

06:11.720 --> 06:13.440
which makes it more convenient for restoration.

06:13.440 --> 06:14.840
This set of restoration tools

06:14.840 --> 06:17.170
looks like it has been used for a long time.

06:17.320 --> 06:18.760
It was a gift from someone.

06:18.760 --> 06:19.360
Who is it?

06:25.000 --> 06:26.060
Let's get started.

06:27.320 --> 06:27.760
Okay.

06:40.880 --> 06:43.000
I hope I can help.

06:44.560 --> 06:45.090
Alright.

06:45.800 --> 06:47.600
Let's start mixing the glue now.

06:49.600 --> 06:52.120
Isn't there ready-made glue?

06:52.920 --> 06:54.200
Different types of porcelain

06:54.200 --> 06:55.360
require different types of

06:55.360 --> 06:56.440
adhesives or glue.

06:56.640 --> 06:57.400
We need to make sure the adhesive

06:57.400 --> 06:58.860
in transparency and color

06:59.800 --> 07:01.440
matches the restored porcelain.

07:01.440 --> 07:03.300
So, it's best to mix it ourselves.

07:04.080 --> 07:04.880
Okay.

07:05.720 --> 07:07.200
Three parts of glue A,

07:07.800 --> 07:09.530
and one part of glue B is enough.

07:12.920 --> 07:13.920
Mix them,

07:14.560 --> 07:15.690
and apply it evenly.

07:17.080 --> 07:17.680
You try it.

07:18.600 --> 07:19.040
Okay.

07:20.160 --> 07:21.220
Put them together,

07:21.400 --> 07:23.330
then use your hands to feel the fit.

07:24.880 --> 07:26.560
Don't put your hands near the gap.

07:26.560 --> 07:27.820
You might get pinched.

07:33.960 --> 07:35.760
Do you know how to apply the tape?

07:36.120 --> 07:37.159
I can do this.

07:38.240 --> 07:39.080
Apply the tape

07:39.400 --> 07:40.930
to make the gap more secure.

07:42.480 --> 07:43.680
What is this thing?

07:44.320 --> 07:44.980
Wax sheets.

07:45.880 --> 07:46.760
Usually,

07:46.960 --> 07:49.690
it's hard to restore the missing parts directly.

07:49.760 --> 07:51.690
So we need to use melted wax sheets.

07:52.120 --> 07:54.580
Then we take its shape from the intact areas.

07:54.920 --> 07:56.640
Get the right ratio of plaster and water.

07:56.640 --> 07:58.370
Add water and stir thoroughly.

07:58.880 --> 08:01.480
The next step is to use its fluidity to fill it in

08:01.640 --> 08:03.240
and shape the rough outline.

08:07.160 --> 08:09.040
This step feels like doing DIY.

08:09.040 --> 08:10.040
Making a cake?

08:11.600 --> 08:13.000
It does look a bit like it.

08:13.040 --> 08:13.640
Mr. Fatty!

08:15.280 --> 08:16.680
Stop yelling. Stop yelling.

08:16.680 --> 08:18.000
I'm coming. I'm coming.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.160
I'll feed you.

08:19.560 --> 08:21.220
Why is there a person up there?

08:22.240 --> 08:24.080
He's probably been here the whole time.

08:24.080 --> 08:24.800
Stop yelling, I'm coming!

08:24.800 --> 08:26.680
Has he been up there the whole time?

08:26.680 --> 08:27.600
Stop yelling, I'm begging you.

08:27.600 --> 08:28.680
Who is he?

08:29.720 --> 08:30.920
The boss of this shop.

08:31.880 --> 08:32.520
Xu,

08:36.039 --> 08:37.640
why is there an extra person?

08:39.080 --> 08:40.010
Something's up.

08:41.039 --> 08:42.240
This is my classmate.

08:42.520 --> 08:44.580
We're doing an assignment together.

08:44.960 --> 08:45.420
Coming.

08:45.600 --> 08:46.660
Coming, Mr. Fatty.

08:48.400 --> 08:50.440
Here, catch.

08:51.480 --> 08:52.340
Don't mind him.

08:52.600 --> 08:53.860
He's always like this.

08:54.400 --> 08:55.240
Let's continue.

08:55.240 --> 08:55.760
Okay.

09:09.520 --> 09:10.920
It's almost done, right?

09:11.000 --> 09:11.860
Not even close.

09:12.200 --> 09:14.160
We still need to use 600- and 2000-grit sandpaper

09:14.160 --> 09:15.290
for fine polishing.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.760
Then we'll use a piece of cowhide dipped in jade polishing powder

09:17.760 --> 09:19.020
for finish polishing.

09:19.680 --> 09:21.720
How long will that take?

09:23.880 --> 09:25.340
When you are restoring it,

09:25.600 --> 09:26.730
what's on your mind?

09:27.520 --> 09:28.650
I was thinking about

09:29.640 --> 09:30.560
restoring it as quickly as possible

09:30.560 --> 09:31.960
so I can finish the assignment.

09:31.960 --> 09:33.440
If you only treat it as an assignment

09:33.440 --> 09:34.400
to be completed,

09:35.040 --> 09:36.300
you won't do a good job.

09:38.080 --> 09:38.480
Oh.

09:41.520 --> 09:42.680
Every restoration

09:43.920 --> 09:45.440
is a conversation between the ceramics

09:45.440 --> 09:46.480
and the restorer.

09:47.840 --> 09:48.960
Every gap,

09:50.000 --> 09:51.560
every tiny crack

09:52.040 --> 09:53.840
is it pouring its heart out to us.

09:54.480 --> 09:56.480
But its voice is very soft and quiet.

09:56.920 --> 09:58.640
Only by feeling it with your heart

09:58.640 --> 10:00.120
can you hear their voices.

10:09.000 --> 10:09.480
Look.

10:10.040 --> 10:12.000
The part restored with plaster

10:12.000 --> 10:13.440
has a huge color difference from the original.

10:13.440 --> 10:15.680
If we make it as close to the original color as possible,

10:15.680 --> 10:17.120
wouldn't it look better?

10:17.480 --> 10:20.040
Coloring is not required for exhibition restorations.

10:20.040 --> 10:20.800
But I

10:21.680 --> 10:25.160
still want to restore it completely.

10:27.080 --> 10:28.960
Do you have any paint here?

10:38.760 --> 10:40.220
You know how to mix colors?

10:40.520 --> 10:42.920
I learned a bit of drawing when I was a kid.

10:43.720 --> 10:44.720
But my mom said

10:44.720 --> 10:46.400
learning to draw was too tiring

10:46.400 --> 10:47.520
and unstable,

10:48.600 --> 10:51.280
so I stopped learning later.

11:11.040 --> 11:12.880
Is it okay?

11:14.000 --> 11:15.260
You are very talented.

11:19.720 --> 11:20.480
Xu Xiao.

11:23.120 --> 11:26.280
Can I take this plate

11:26.920 --> 11:28.400
home tonight?

11:28.920 --> 11:29.600
Sure.

11:52.720 --> 11:53.160
Mom.

11:53.320 --> 11:54.000
Cencen,

11:55.400 --> 11:56.000
come here.

11:56.920 --> 11:57.680
I washed some grapes for you.

11:57.680 --> 11:58.160
Okay.

11:58.840 --> 12:00.040
Mom, look at my plate.

12:01.280 --> 12:02.440
It looks nice.

12:02.520 --> 12:05.600
You've shown it to me several times since you got back today.

12:05.600 --> 12:06.480
Are you tired?

12:06.520 --> 12:08.120
You've been doing it all day.

12:08.200 --> 12:08.800
Not tired.

12:09.920 --> 12:11.440
Studying is important,

12:11.600 --> 12:13.120
but your health is more important.

12:13.120 --> 12:14.000
Without a healthy body,

12:14.000 --> 12:15.200
nothing has meaning.

12:15.600 --> 12:17.600
So don't exhaust yourself too much.

12:17.800 --> 12:18.320
I know.

12:19.600 --> 12:20.930
Here, have some grapes.

12:23.280 --> 12:24.610
Here, you have some too.

12:30.520 --> 12:32.200
Yours is too rough.

12:32.200 --> 12:33.200
It's unqualified.

12:33.200 --> 12:34.480
Teacher, what about ours?

12:34.480 --> 12:35.600
Yours is also too rough.

12:35.600 --> 12:36.660
It's unqualified.

12:37.760 --> 12:39.560
What is that gray stuff on your plate?

12:39.560 --> 12:40.440
Plasticine.

12:40.600 --> 12:42.400
You use this to repair the damaged part?

12:42.400 --> 12:42.960
Smart, right?

12:42.960 --> 12:44.890
How is it? It saves trouble, right?

12:45.240 --> 12:47.080
It will deform when Mr. Yue squeezes it later.

12:47.080 --> 12:48.000
Let's see what you do.

12:48.000 --> 12:48.640
Exactly.

12:49.040 --> 12:49.600
Xu Xiao.

12:50.040 --> 12:51.320
Have you repaired your porcelain plate?

12:51.320 --> 12:52.120
Right, right.

12:53.800 --> 12:55.080
When did you restore it?

12:55.080 --> 12:56.560
I didn't see you in the Restoration Room.

12:56.560 --> 12:57.600
We restored it off-campus.

12:57.600 --> 13:00.000
You actually met up off-campus privately.

13:00.040 --> 13:02.120
We just went to finish our assignment.

13:02.120 --> 13:02.880
Really?

13:04.720 --> 13:06.000
Come, let me see yours.

13:06.200 --> 13:07.600
This is all dented.

13:07.600 --> 13:08.600
It fails.

13:09.400 --> 13:10.760
Failed again.

13:10.880 --> 13:12.120
Let me see yours.

13:12.960 --> 13:14.040
I wonder how many people

13:14.040 --> 13:15.160
Mr. Yue will pass this time.

13:15.160 --> 13:16.120
I heard

13:16.160 --> 13:18.080
no one can get credits from his class.

13:18.080 --> 13:19.320
I really tried my best this time.

13:19.320 --> 13:19.800
Yeah.

13:19.800 --> 13:21.440
What do you call this?

13:21.440 --> 13:22.200
Failed.

13:23.000 --> 13:23.920
Failed again.

13:23.920 --> 13:24.920
I told you so.

13:25.120 --> 13:26.200
It wouldn't work.

13:26.240 --> 13:27.040
Failed.

13:27.840 --> 13:29.040
Let me see yours.

13:30.560 --> 13:31.600
Yours is not bad.

13:31.880 --> 13:33.960
You even touched up the colors yourself.

13:33.960 --> 13:35.120
Not bad. Pretty good.

13:35.120 --> 13:35.560
Thank you, sir.

13:35.560 --> 13:36.240
Passed.

13:36.840 --> 13:38.370
What's our score this time?

13:38.800 --> 13:40.000
What was it last time?

13:40.000 --> 13:41.400
Last time was 65.

13:42.120 --> 13:42.920
Seventy.

13:43.280 --> 13:44.640
Alright, class.

13:44.680 --> 13:46.400
Put your plates down,

13:46.400 --> 13:47.660
face down on the table.

13:48.040 --> 13:50.640
Pick up the small hammer on your workbench.

13:51.840 --> 13:52.640
No way.

13:52.920 --> 13:54.080
Yeah, here we go again.

13:54.080 --> 13:55.610
Come on, pick up the hammer.

13:55.760 --> 13:56.760
The hammer again?

13:57.040 --> 13:57.640
What's wrong?

13:57.640 --> 13:59.200
We worked so hard to fix this.

13:59.200 --> 14:00.000
I can't bear to do it.

14:00.000 --> 14:00.960
Stop complaining.

14:00.960 --> 14:01.280
Come on.

14:01.280 --> 14:01.960
Then let me do it.

14:01.960 --> 14:02.920
Three, two, one, smash it.

14:02.920 --> 14:03.320
Let's do this.

14:03.320 --> 14:04.160
I don't get it.

14:04.600 --> 14:04.960
Come on.

14:04.960 --> 14:06.400
Alright, step aside.

14:06.880 --> 14:08.280
Watch out for the shards.

14:08.520 --> 14:08.960
Collecting them again.

14:08.960 --> 14:09.800
Watch your hands.

14:09.800 --> 14:10.760
Watch your hands.

14:10.760 --> 14:11.280
Here.

14:11.280 --> 14:13.610
I've collected all the porcelain pieces.

14:13.800 --> 14:14.760
Here. Okay.

14:14.760 --> 14:15.200
So many.

14:15.200 --> 14:16.800
Why are you taking them all away?

14:16.800 --> 14:19.260
All the pieces of the broken plates are here.

14:19.400 --> 14:21.320
Can you guys, in just one class,

14:21.760 --> 14:23.680
restore your porcelain plates?

14:23.680 --> 14:24.160
Impossible.

14:24.160 --> 14:25.840
Help, I can't do this at all.

14:25.920 --> 14:26.480
How is that possible?

14:26.480 --> 14:27.760
This is too difficult.

14:27.760 --> 14:28.160
Yeah.

14:28.480 --> 14:30.840
We couldn't even finish the simpler tasks

14:30.840 --> 14:32.160
from the first two classes.

14:32.160 --> 14:32.880
Yeah.

14:33.080 --> 14:34.140
Let alone you guys,

14:34.760 --> 14:35.960
even if experts came,

14:36.520 --> 14:38.320
it would be very difficult to do.

14:38.520 --> 14:39.560
After the founding of the PRC,

14:39.560 --> 14:40.960
our archaeology workers

14:41.080 --> 14:42.740
unearthed a massive amount of

14:42.920 --> 14:46.450
Ming Dynasty blue-and-white porcelain dragon jar fragments.

14:47.040 --> 14:49.720
So many that several warehouses couldn't hold them.

14:49.720 --> 14:50.760
But up to now,

14:51.040 --> 14:53.720
how many do you think have been restored?

14:53.720 --> 14:54.520
100.

14:55.000 --> 14:55.760
200.

14:55.760 --> 14:56.560
20.

14:56.560 --> 14:56.960
10.

14:56.960 --> 14:57.800
None of them.

14:58.400 --> 14:59.120
Up to now,

14:59.960 --> 15:03.240
only 3 pieces have been restored.

15:03.440 --> 15:04.400
3?

15:04.520 --> 15:04.920
Yes.

15:06.760 --> 15:08.420
Cultural relics restoration

15:08.920 --> 15:11.160
takes a long time.

15:11.760 --> 15:13.720
and a persevering attitude.

15:14.640 --> 15:15.840
In these two classes,

15:15.840 --> 15:17.320
you have experienced three times

15:17.320 --> 15:19.250
of tearing down and starting over.

15:19.400 --> 15:20.480
Such a process

15:20.560 --> 15:22.440
in your future lives

15:22.480 --> 15:24.610
will be experienced countless times.

15:24.640 --> 15:25.400
Class,

15:25.680 --> 15:26.800
I hope that

15:27.160 --> 15:28.640
since you have come to this class,

15:28.640 --> 15:29.700
You must establish

15:29.760 --> 15:33.090
the determination to dedicate your life to this profession

15:33.400 --> 15:34.760
and deeply experience

15:35.200 --> 15:38.320
what cultural relics restoration really is.

15:44.760 --> 15:45.480
Let's go.

15:45.480 --> 15:46.440
My legs are sore

15:46.640 --> 15:47.680
from going out for the first time.

15:47.680 --> 15:48.280
Me too.

15:48.480 --> 15:49.840
Let's go get some milk tea.

15:49.840 --> 15:50.800
Cheer up.

15:50.800 --> 15:51.930
What is this called?

15:52.320 --> 15:53.120
Overcoming difficulties.

15:53.120 --> 15:53.880
Okay.

15:54.320 --> 15:55.320
I'm leaving. Bye.

15:55.640 --> 15:56.400
I want half sugar.

15:56.400 --> 15:57.960
Let's go to that same place. Okay?

15:57.960 --> 15:58.960
That place again?

15:59.120 --> 16:00.640
But I think their stuff is good.

16:00.640 --> 16:01.240
Let's go.

16:01.240 --> 16:01.770
Let's go.

16:02.320 --> 16:03.180
My treat today.

16:03.320 --> 16:03.920
Heading home.

16:03.920 --> 16:04.640
Thank you, young master.

16:04.640 --> 16:05.040
Bye.

16:05.040 --> 16:05.880
Bye, bye.

16:15.240 --> 16:16.040
Zhao Xiaocen.

16:19.280 --> 16:19.880
Hold this.

16:21.440 --> 16:22.000
Thanks.

16:23.920 --> 16:25.720
What were you doing just now?

16:26.560 --> 16:28.690
Because it was hard to piece together,

16:30.200 --> 16:30.760
so...

16:31.240 --> 16:33.370
Do you think you can piece it together?

16:34.240 --> 16:35.040
I...

16:39.600 --> 16:41.000
Let's connect on WeChat.

16:43.040 --> 16:43.770
Is that okay?

16:44.120 --> 16:45.160
S-Sure.

17:15.319 --> 17:17.040
Thank you for the band-aid.

17:22.119 --> 17:23.050
You're welcome.

17:24.800 --> 17:25.460
Good night.

17:26.319 --> 17:27.119
Good night.

17:27.800 --> 17:28.640
Xu Xiao.

17:29.320 --> 17:31.480
What kind of person are you exactly?

17:32.800 --> 17:34.860
What kind of profile picture is this?

17:35.680 --> 17:38.210
Why hasn't he posted anything on his Moments?

17:43.400 --> 17:44.320
I'm doomed.

17:59.400 --> 18:00.200
Time to sleep.

18:04.080 --> 18:05.080
Mr. Liang announced that

18:05.080 --> 18:07.280
we will visit the Imperial Kiln Museum this Friday.

18:07.280 --> 18:09.740
Gather at the school gate at 8:00 a.m. sharp.

18:16.160 --> 18:16.960
My name is...

18:18.200 --> 18:19.530
My name is Zhao Xiaocen.

18:21.960 --> 18:23.760
Sir, I don't know what to say.

18:24.160 --> 18:24.520
Okay.

18:24.520 --> 18:25.080
Cheers!

18:25.080 --> 18:26.480
Come on, cheers! Cheers!

18:26.720 --> 18:27.320
Come on.

18:27.320 --> 18:27.650
Okay.

18:27.840 --> 18:29.240
Cheers, cheers, cheers!

18:32.160 --> 18:33.880
Let's add each other on WeChat.

18:33.880 --> 18:34.640
Is that okay?

18:36.480 --> 18:38.840
How exactly does everyone see me?

18:52.440 --> 18:53.280
This is the place.

18:53.280 --> 18:54.320
Look over there.

18:54.320 --> 18:55.160
It's so big.

18:55.760 --> 18:56.800
It's beautiful.

18:57.040 --> 18:58.040
I come here often.

18:58.120 --> 18:58.920
It looks so fancy.

18:58.920 --> 19:00.320
Students, this is

19:00.320 --> 19:02.640
the director of the Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum,

19:02.640 --> 19:03.500
Director Zhou.

19:03.800 --> 19:04.600
Hello, Director.

19:04.600 --> 19:05.600
Hello, students.

19:05.680 --> 19:08.410
Welcome to the Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum.

19:08.600 --> 19:09.920
This visit

19:10.120 --> 19:11.320
is jointly organized

19:11.480 --> 19:13.610
by the museum and Ceramic University.

19:13.960 --> 19:15.640
I am glad to see so many

19:15.840 --> 19:18.000
young people interested in cultural relics

19:18.000 --> 19:19.400
and their conservation.

19:19.600 --> 19:20.720
Our museum

19:20.960 --> 19:23.760
houses over a thousand pieces of rejected tribute porcelain

19:23.760 --> 19:26.320
from the Yuan, Ming, and Qing imperial kilns,

19:26.320 --> 19:29.480
restored by the Jingdezhen Institute of Ceramic Archaeology.

19:29.480 --> 19:31.840
Many of them are unique and unmatchable.

19:32.240 --> 19:33.800
It's safe to say that one day

19:33.800 --> 19:35.960
isn't enough to see everything thoroughly.

19:35.960 --> 19:38.880
So, I welcome you all

19:38.960 --> 19:40.760
to visit our museum often when you have time.

19:40.760 --> 19:41.720
Okay.

19:42.040 --> 19:43.000
Now,

19:43.280 --> 19:45.400
let me show you around personally.

19:45.640 --> 19:46.640
Okay.

19:46.640 --> 19:47.240
Let's go. This way.

19:47.240 --> 19:48.500
Sorry for the trouble.

19:49.240 --> 19:51.400
The display and design of the Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum...

19:51.400 --> 19:53.680
The layout features connected display cases

19:53.680 --> 19:55.280
alongside individual ones.

19:55.560 --> 19:56.560
Each exhibit

19:56.560 --> 19:58.960
is accompanied by a plaque in both Chinese and English.

19:58.960 --> 20:01.320
You can follow these materials

20:01.560 --> 20:02.820
to keep up with my pace.

20:03.960 --> 20:04.440
Come on.

20:04.440 --> 20:05.500
Keep up, everyone.

20:05.880 --> 20:07.200
Let's go to the exhibition hall over there.

20:07.200 --> 20:08.800
Thank you for your hard work, Director Zhou.

20:08.800 --> 20:09.730
You have no idea.

20:14.080 --> 20:15.560
A cricket pot.

20:16.120 --> 20:17.880
This can also be considered a cultural relic?

20:17.880 --> 20:20.040
These are cricket pots from the Xuande reign of the Ming Dynasty.

20:20.040 --> 20:21.720
Emperor Xuande loved cricket fighting very much.

20:21.720 --> 20:23.650
This student is absolutely right.

20:23.720 --> 20:25.960
Among the people, there are sayings of the "Peaceful Emperor"

20:25.960 --> 20:27.640
and the "Cricket Emperor,"

20:27.720 --> 20:29.450
which refer to Emperor Xuande.

20:29.840 --> 20:32.080
Emperor Xuanzong died of illness at the age of 36.

20:32.080 --> 20:36.040
His eldest son, Zhu Qizhen, succeeded the throne at only eight years old.

20:36.040 --> 20:37.700
Grand Empress Dowager Zhang,

20:37.880 --> 20:39.560
to prevent the young emperor

20:39.640 --> 20:41.920
from becoming obsessed with playthings like his father,

20:41.920 --> 20:45.380
ordered all entertaining items to be removed from the palace.

20:46.040 --> 20:47.520
The cricket pots from the Xuande reign

20:47.520 --> 20:49.400
were thus mostly destroyed.

20:49.800 --> 20:50.640
Later on,

20:50.680 --> 20:53.720
several pieces of blue-and-white porcelain were discovered in Jingdezhen,

20:53.720 --> 20:57.000
allowing these Xuande cricket pots to be restored.

20:59.080 --> 21:01.240
Even the emperor has someone to keep him in check.

21:01.240 --> 21:04.900
No matter what official you are, your mom still bosses you around.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.200
All right, that's all for today's explanation.

21:09.200 --> 21:11.120
I hope through your visit today,

21:11.240 --> 21:13.680
you will fall in love with the imperial kiln and Jingdezhen.

21:13.680 --> 21:14.840
Thank you, Director Zhou.

21:14.840 --> 21:16.120
For the rest of the time,

21:16.120 --> 21:17.000
you can move around freely.

21:17.000 --> 21:17.840
Feel free to explore

21:17.840 --> 21:18.840
wherever you want.

21:18.840 --> 21:19.560
Okay.

21:19.560 --> 21:20.480
Director Zhou, after you.

21:20.480 --> 21:21.120
Okay.

21:26.240 --> 21:26.640
Wu Jing.

21:26.640 --> 21:27.200
Coming.

21:27.200 --> 21:28.200
Come look at this.

21:28.200 --> 21:30.040
Wow, this is so pretty.

21:30.400 --> 21:31.440
It's beautiful.

21:33.760 --> 21:34.600
Look at this.

21:36.600 --> 21:37.840
There's a duck over there.

21:37.840 --> 21:38.720
A duck?

21:39.680 --> 21:40.480
Pretty.

21:44.120 --> 21:44.840
Like this.

21:45.880 --> 21:46.440
Come.

21:47.520 --> 21:49.080
Three, two, one.

21:49.960 --> 21:50.440
Look at this.

21:50.440 --> 21:51.040
Let me see.

21:54.280 --> 21:56.340
Three-Interconnected-Pot Vessel.

21:57.120 --> 21:58.520
What is this used for?

22:01.320 --> 22:03.520
This is a great unsolved mystery in ceramics.

22:03.520 --> 22:05.450
Ordinary people can't answer you.

22:06.440 --> 22:08.400
Regarding this Three-Interconnected-Pot Vessel,

22:08.400 --> 22:09.720
it lacks documentary records,

22:09.720 --> 22:11.960
and there are no related artifacts for reference.

22:11.960 --> 22:14.600
So the academic community has different opinions on its usage.

22:14.600 --> 22:17.060
Some say it is a medical and sanitary device,

22:17.120 --> 22:19.840
and others say it is an offering vessel in a mosque.

22:19.840 --> 22:21.570
But there is no relevant basis.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.530
You are also a visitor. How do you know so much?

22:25.320 --> 22:27.000
Maybe this is my profession.

22:29.240 --> 22:29.720
Yuexin,

22:30.200 --> 22:32.200
let's take a photo with Ducktor Sui.

22:32.320 --> 22:32.560
Okay.

22:32.560 --> 22:32.890
Come.

22:34.080 --> 22:34.640
Come on.

22:35.080 --> 22:35.540
Coming.

22:37.920 --> 22:38.960
Three, two, one.

23:41.520 --> 23:42.580
What are you doing?

23:48.160 --> 23:50.840
This wall can make sounds.

23:51.840 --> 23:52.770
Didn't you know?

23:55.080 --> 23:57.540
The walls of the entire Imperial Kiln Museum

23:57.640 --> 23:59.170
are built with kiln bricks.

24:00.000 --> 24:01.730
Tapping the kiln bricks gently

24:01.840 --> 24:04.570
causes resonance in the gaps between the bricks,

24:08.680 --> 24:10.280
producing a pleasant sound.

24:12.440 --> 24:13.640
This entire museum

24:14.640 --> 24:16.000
is like an instrument.

24:27.000 --> 24:28.000
Did you hear that?

24:49.040 --> 24:50.300
Do you have time today?

25:03.640 --> 25:04.370
You're here.

25:07.840 --> 25:09.500
I prepared something for you.

25:09.800 --> 25:10.800
Have a seat first.

25:10.880 --> 25:11.680
Wait a moment.

25:38.400 --> 25:39.960
I saw the previous plate was broken,

25:39.960 --> 25:41.490
and you weren't very happy.

25:42.080 --> 25:43.280
So based on my memory

25:43.320 --> 25:44.640
of its size and style,

25:44.920 --> 25:46.050
I made a similar one.

25:47.440 --> 25:49.100
This is just an unglazed body.

25:49.120 --> 25:52.380
It will look very similar to the previous one after firing.

25:54.240 --> 25:56.640
Are you saying you can bring it back to life?

25:57.320 --> 25:58.840
Bring it back to life is an exaggeration.

25:58.840 --> 25:59.760
But if you want,

26:00.280 --> 26:02.680
we can paint it with the original patterns.

26:02.920 --> 26:04.050
You can do it anyway.

26:09.280 --> 26:10.080
What's wrong?

26:10.880 --> 26:11.410
Nothing.

26:47.800 --> 26:50.060
Then the next step is glazing and firing.

26:52.880 --> 26:54.200
Let's give it a name.

26:54.960 --> 26:55.560
A name?

26:57.080 --> 26:58.640
Don't all the porcelains in the museum

26:58.640 --> 26:59.720
have names?

27:00.920 --> 27:02.480
We fired it together.

27:03.040 --> 27:04.700
I think it's very meaningful.

27:06.320 --> 27:07.160
How about

27:09.280 --> 27:10.840
Fish Play Among the Lotus Leaves?

27:10.840 --> 27:13.800
Can't you give it a shorter name?

27:19.680 --> 27:21.440
Then call it Xiao Qing.

27:22.240 --> 27:23.360
Xiao Qing?

27:26.320 --> 27:26.800
Sure.
